<p></p></div>
<div class=3D"faq">
<p><strong>Q5: Why do we need square root in real life?</strong></p>
<p>Answer: Square root has many applications from Hero=E2=80=99s formula to=
 the Pythagoras theorem for finding the area when the lengths are given or =
we can say that sides are shared. It is very useful in architecture, engine=
ering work and the construction of anything, especially bridges constructio=
n and last but not least in carpentering work.</p>
<p></p></div>
